Two models benchmarked:

  (a) FULL encoder+decoder greedy-decode graph from
      https://huggingface.co/nyadla-sys/whisper-tiny.en.tflite
      file: whisper-tiny.en.tflite (41,507,968 B, fp32)
      input:  serving_default_input_features:0  [1, 80, 3000] fp32
      output: StatefulPartitionedCall:0         [1, 449]     int32  (token ids)

  (b) ENCODER-ONLY fp32 TFLite built fresh in-session (NNAPI refused (a)
      outright — see below). Pipeline:
          HF transformers openai/whisper-tiny.en  .get_encoder()
        -> torch.onnx.export (opset 14, static shape 1x80x3000)
        -> onnx-graphsurgeon: rewrite every Erf(y) as
              tanh(1.12838*y + 0.04451*y^3)   (polynomial GELU approx)
           (onnx2tf otherwise emits tf.math.erf, which is a TF-Select
            op "FlexErf" and the stripped benchmark_model binary does
            NOT link the Flex delegate.)
        -> onnx2tf (float32 + float16 output)
      file: whisper_enc_tiny_en_fp32.tflite (32,881,808 B, 262 ops)
      input:  mel [1, 80, 3000] fp32
      output: enc_out [1, 1500, 384] fp32


